@Node SYNOPSIS "ASwarm/Synopsis"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
   SYS:WBStartup/ASwarm

@{b}Synopsis@{ub}
   ASwarm
      @{"CX_PRIORITY/N/K    " Link TOOLTYPES 5}  =<System Priority>
      @{"CX_POPKEY/K        " Link TOOLTYPES 13}  =<@{"Hot Key Description String" Link HOTKEY}>
      @{"CX_POPUP/S         " Link TOOLTYPES 7}  =<No parameter>
      @{"BLANKKEY/K         " Link TOOLTYPES 17}  =<@{"Hot Key Description String" Link HOTKEY}>
      @{"SECONDS=TIMEOUT/N/K" Link TOOLTYPES 21}  =<1 - 3600>
      @{"CLIENTTIMEOUT/N/K  " Link TOOLTYPES 27}  =<1 - 60>
      @{"DISPLAY/K          " Link TOOLTYPES 33}  =<@{"Display Resolution" Link DISPLAY}>
      @{"CYCLE/S            " Link TOOLTYPES 38}  =<YES | NO>
      @{"AIM/S              " Link TOOLTYPES 41}  =<YES | NO>
      @{"WASPS/N/K          " Link TOOLTYPES 44}  =<1 - 10>
      @{"BEES/N/K           " Link TOOLTYPES 47}  =<1 - 500>
      @{"SPEED/N/K          " Link TOOLTYPES 50}  =<1 - 4>
      @{"TIGHTNESS/N/K      " Link TOOLTYPES 53}  =<1 - 10>
      @{"VELOCITY/N/K       " Link TOOLTYPES 67}  =<1 - 15>
      @{"MOUSEBLANKMETHOD/K " Link TOOLTYPES 58}  =<Hardware | Window>
      @{"JOYSTICK/S         " Link TOOLTYPES 80}  =<YES | NO>
      @{"FINALTIMEOUT/N/K   " Link TOOLTYPES 75}  =<0 | 1 - 3600>
@EndNode

@Node DESCRIPTION "ASwarm/Description"
@{b}Description@{ub}

A  Screenblanker  with high security which does not burn
in  the graphic into the screen when CPU is really busy.
It's  funny  to watch, runs @{i}only@{ui} under Amiga OS
Release 2.04 or newer. Needs the @{"MUI" Link MUI} User-
Interface.

@EndNode

@Node SOURCE "ASwarm/Source"
@{b}Source@{ub}

The  source  code  is  included, it can be compiled with
SAS-C 5.10a (or newer) or with the registered version of
Dice V2.06.54 (or newer).

The  source  is included to give you a chance to use the
Client/Server  model  of ASwarm II, or to look how we've
done  the  Commodity  Interface.   Please @{i}don't@{ui}
spread  your  improved  versions  of ASwarm II under the
name  of ASwarm, because this may confuse the public and
it's not fair.

@EndNode

